          "id": "a0e1c6143768_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8f4a",
          "text": "Water is used by agriculture, industry and municipalities. Unsustainable extraction from aquifers lowers the groundwater level. Within a bioregion it is good to assess the water budget — inflows and outflows. Sustainable communities can then ensure they are using water from sustainable sources and conserving wherever possible (see picture Conceptual Water Budget).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 30,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "a0e1c6143768_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "73fe",
          "text": "Source & More on Water Budgets",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*7SACVxxrbgt2Bb0X27hqiQ.gif",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 6,
              "href": "http://water.state.co.us/SurfaceWater/SWRights/PublishingImages/WATBUDG.GIF",
              "rel": "",
